inn1.comm: drifting on to the pads. Jacques tries to flick it away, doesn't connect and it runs off the pads to the leg side

Almost a run-out! Jacques stumbled as he went for a run, after flicking it to right of Dwayne Bravo at square-leg, and if Bravo throw had hit the sticks, Jacques would have been on his bike.In fact he lost his shoe.
landed on a length, on the middle and off, and came in with the angle and beat the intended poke and thudded into the thigh pads
Down the leg side. And also it didnt carry to the keeper
Landed on a length, and straightened. Katich pats it back to the bowler
another length  ball and it kept a touch low. Nothing alarming mind you. tapped to the off side
After again knocking off the bails on his delivery stride for the second ball in succession, Bradshaw runs in again. another length ball, just outside the off stump, played quietly to covers
Good ball first up. landed on a length, around the off stump, a 85.5mph delivery, Jacques goes back to tap it gently to the off side
hit the deck around the off stump, kicked up, Jacques let it come to him, cut it past gully, out to the third man
Beaten! landed short of a length, outside the offstump and kicked up. Slash and a miss.
on the legs.... attmepted to flick it away , runs off the pad.to shortish fineleg
drifting down the leg side. Also, again, it kept low and went to the keeper on a bounce.
landed on a length, outside the off stump, left alone
beaten! landed on a length, just outside the off stump, a nervous poke
just outside the off stump, slightly short of length, Katich goes back and across, places it wide of the third man for a single

clean bowled!  Got him! Full, swinging in and that was enough. It came back in the air, landed on the middle and off, and Jacques tries to go for a off drive is beaten by the movement in and the ball threads the bat and pad gap to crash into the stumps
Attempted yorker goes awry. way down the leg side
full and outside the off stump, Ponting lets it go through to the wicket keeper
fullish and hint of out swing. Ponting is ready, leans forward, waits for the swing and pushes it straight down the track, past the bowler
Edwards dragged back the length this time. Slightly short of a length, outside the off stump, Ponting goes back and across, plays it quietly to the off side
hit the deck, around a length, on the off and middle, Ponting goes back, turns the ball to Lara at midwicket

Almost a run-out again! It was fullish on the middle and leg, Katich tries to turn it on to the leg side but is beaten by the swing, the ball runs to point where Dwayne smith picks the cherry and hurls it on the non-strikers  end and if it had hit, that would have been hit
on a length, around the off stump, Ponting comes forward and pushes it to the covers
fullish, on the legs and that's bread and butter for Ponting. He leans forward, turns the ball past midwicket
another overpitched delivery but this time on the off stump line. Ponting leans forward and drives it to mid-off
angled across Ponting who keeps his left foot out, covers the stumps and shoulders arms.
fidel to katich. short and rising. hit the deck around the off stump and kicked up chest high. Katich was made to hop, took his bottom hand out of the handle,and steered it to third man
lovely flick. it was on the middle and leg, Ponting waited for the ball to arrive, turned his wrists and tickled it down to the fine-leg fence.
fullish on the off stump line, pushed to mid-off
on the corridor of uncertainity, Ponting thrusts his left foot forward, covers the stumps and then, shoulders arms
landed slightly short of length, outside the off stump and it held its line. Ponting tried to force it off the back foot, but didtn connect well and the ball rolls to the covers
fullish and well outside the off stump. Ponting reaches for it and throws the kitchen sink at it and the ball gets the outside edge, goes in the air but over the point fielder and thats that.
down the leg side, attempted flick, doesn't connect
fullish on the middle and the off stump, came in with the angle, pushed to the on side
Another one that drifts aimlessly down the leg side. Bradshaw is having some problem here
this time he gets his radar right, hurls one outside the off stump, Katich pokes at it, doesn't get a touch and the ball dies down on its way to the keeper
fullish, on the off and middle, Katich stays at his crease, pushes the ball towards cover
slightly shorter this time, and it ended up just outside the off stump and kept a touch low as well. Ponting went back, adjusted the low-bounce and tapped it to point
gentle floater outside the off stump, overpitched as well... and Katich reached out and drove it past point
slightly shorter, on the middle stump, cut to point
similar ball, same result
much slower this time, on the middle, Katich has to wait for an eternity for the ball to arrive, pats it back to the bowler
beaten! this on had the nip off the pitch, landed on the off stump line, turned past the bat
outside the off stump and driven to the cover fence
landed on the middle stump, and suddenly jumped up - bit of variable bounce on display- and Katich did well to play it with soft hands and placed it to the on side
overpitched and well outside the offstump and Ponting would have put it away in his sleep. Flashed to the cover fence
landed on a length, just outside the offstump, Ponting went back and tried to force it off the back foot, gets an outside but luckily, for him, it doesnt carry to the keeper
attempted sweep but doesn't connect
on the leg and middle line, turned to short fine-leg
floated on the middle stump, pl,ayed back quietly down the track
hurled quick on the leg side, tickled to short fine-leg again,
again turned straight to short fine-leg and there is no chance of a run
flat, quick and on the middle stump line, Katich pats it back to the bowler
starts off well. fullish on the middle stump and it held its line which surprised Ponting. He was attempting to whip it across the line and ends up edging it to point instead
on the legs and turned past square-leg
short of length delivery, on the off stump, Katich who was on his back and across movement was initially cramped a bit but managed to lean back, and cut it to third man
another good ball, just outside the off stump and it held its line, Ponting pushed at it with a open face of the bat and it went in the air, through the vacant third slip region, for a single
short and well outside the offstump, Katich rocks back to cut it past point
in an effort to get the line right, he ends up drifting it down the leg side
fullish and on the middle and leg stump, Katich turns it to midwicket, wants a run but Ponting sends him back
short and wide, cut past point where the fielder dived to his left, gets an hand to it but doesn't stop it completely and they run two.

Oh ho! a snorter. A perfume ball as they say. It climbed up at his throat, Ponting shaped for a hook but was caught unawares by the pace and the lift, just about manages to get an upper edge, over the keeper....
another short one attempted but this time it didn't have that carry and Ponting rocks back and pulls it with panache
another good delviery, hit the deck, short of length, around the off stump and kicked up.. Ponting pushed at it and was surprised by the bounce and the ball hits the top of the bat and runs to point
Majestic pull. Short again but not that kind of alarming bounce and Ponting pulls it, as only he can, to midwicket fence
slanted across Katich who tries to tickle it to third man, doesn't get a touch and is beaten
Even better delivery, landed on a length, around the off stump but Katich was not going to fish around this time, lets it go through
beaten! another one slanting across, landed on a length and kept a touch low and also, I suspect, a little slow and Katich has a poke at it
on the pads, attempted flick, doesn't connect and the ball runs off the pads towards fine-leg

Wonderful wonderful shot. It landed short of length, outside the offstump and suddenly kicked up, but Ponting waited for it, leant back, and then, cleverly, tapped the ball over the slips. A skillful shot.
short of length, on the off stump line, pushed to point
It would have been a nice ball for a right-hand batsman, not for Katich. Down the leg side and wide called.   27 runs came in the last three overs
again on the pads, fullish, Katich comes inside the line, waits for the ball to arrive, and uses his wrists to send the ball, along the ground, past square-leg
better delivery. Landed short of length, on the leg and middle line, and kicked up and crashed into the thigh pad
short of length but outside the leg stump and it held its line, Katich tried to flick it away, doesn't get a touch and the ball brushes the thigh pad enroute to the keeper
on the pads, Ponting tries to get inside the line and push it to the on side but doesnt get a touch and it runs off the pads to the on side and they cross through for a quick single
down the leg side again. The West Indian quicks have been quite erratic
it was fullish and on the leg and middle. Katich stood where he was, and the last minute worked his wrists overtime to send the ball to fine-leg
overpitched on the leg and middle stump and Katich, as his wont, works it past square-leg
in the channel around the off stump, Ponting leans forward, covers his stumps and shoulders arms
overpitched on the middle stump, Ponting leans forward and push-drives it to mid-on
slight short of length, on the off and middle, Ponting works it to the right of mid-on
short and wide, should have put that away and Katich did try, attempted an square-cut but hits it straight to point
on a length, around the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
fullish on the legs. attempted flick but does't make proper contact and the ball runs down to shortish fine-leg
way down the leg side. That was the 15 th extra of the innings
pushed to right of mid-off and they hurry through for a quick single
on a length, pushed back to the bowler
fullish and on the pads, turned past square-leg
a length-delivery, worked to third man
A length-delivery, on the off stump line, Katich goes back and across, gets adjacent to the line to push the ball to covers
slightly short of a length, on the leg side and Katich goes back, tries to whip it past midwicket but finds the fielder.
short of length, on the off stump line and slanting away, pushed to gully
short of length, around the off stump line, Katich hops back and punch-drives it to mid-off and they hurry through for a quick single
hmm... another wide one, down the leg side. The disease continues to permeate the West Indies team
overpitched delivery and Ponting eases it past covers
landed on a length, around the middle stump line, moved towards off, turned to point
fullish, and outside the off stump. Katich goes down on his knees, goes for an extravagant square-drive but doesn't connect properly and the ball runs to point
pushed to co vers
on the legs, Katich doesn't get a bat on to it, and the ball runs off the pads to shortish fine-leg
overpitched on the middle stump line, Ponting leans forward, pushes it to right of the mid-on and an easy single results.
fullish, on the middle and leg,  Katich whips it towards left of mid-on where a fumbling dive is attempted. Two runs result.
length delivery on the off stump and it comes in a touch. Ponting goes back and is cramped a bit but pushes it to point

Oh ho! Ponting dances down the track, in an effort to break free, Smith holds the ball back a bit, it lands on the middle, veers in and Ponting goes for a mighty heave but doesn't connect and it raps him on the pads.
outside the off stump, short of a length, punched past point
overpitched delivery, pusehd to mid-on
down the leg side, tickled to fine-leg fence
fullish and wide outside the off stump, Ponting reaches for it and crashes it over cover
pushed to cover
full and outside the off stump, driven to mid-off
again, on the off stump line, punch-driven to mid-off
short of length, just outside the off stump, Katich leans back to force it past point
overpitched on the leg and middle, turned to mid-on

Got his man! It landed on a length, on the middle and off stump line and held its line, Ponting went back and was surprised as the ball skidded low after landing and was caught in front of his off stump. It didnt roll along the ground, mind you, but kept a touch low and maybe it was a delivery that Ponting should have gone forward to.
overpitched outside the off stump, Katich goes down on his knees, crashes it past cover
attempted yorker, right up to the batsman, on the off and middle line, punched back to the bowler.
fullish, outside the off stump, hint of away swing and Clarke reaches for it and has a slash. The ball flies off an outside edge, past point.
another wide. Lara must be going crazy
overpitched on the off and middle and Clarke whips it across, to midwicket
Clarke recieves a good-length delivery that landed just outside the off stump and held its line. He leans forward, covers the line and pushes it to point
Wonderful push-drive that sent the ball along the turf between cover and mid-off. He leaned forward, and drove it on the up, the left elbow high and all that jazz. Beautiful to watch.
punched past point for a single
landed on a length, around the middle and off and Clarke pushed at it. The ball runs down to third man area
short of length, on the middle stump line, coming in with the angle. Katich stands tall, whips it to midwicket
the line went slightly awry this time, on the hips, Katich got inside the line, tickled it fine, very fine, and Wavell Hinds gets across quickly and prevents a second run.
pushed to cover
another wide. slanted across Clarke, Will Clarke have a go? He thrust his left foot across, to the pitch of the ball but decided against anything flashy and let the ball go through.
pushed to right of mid-on and they jog through for a single
short of a length, quite slow, on the off, worked away to midwicket off the back foot
once again clipped to the leg side
defended watchfully back down the pitch
eased towards mid-on
placed just wide of square-leg for a single
short of a good length and outside the off, eased down towards long-on for a single

fullish and on the stumps, Katich tries to hit the ball through the leg side but closes the face of the bat early, the ball spears off the leading edge and goes straight up in the air for Dwayne Bravo to safely catch at mid-off!
Clarke is facing as the batsmen crossed over during the catch, short of a good length, outside the off, left alone to the keeper
full and quite straight, Clarke drives handsomely and hard but straight to mid-on
fullish and outside the off, eased just wide of point with an angled bat for a single
fullish and on the off, Cosgrove watches that one carefully and defends to off
full once more and on the off, driven along the ground to mid off
short and pulled away fiercely but a good diving stop at square-leg prevents any run
slower this time and much fuller, Clarke waits for the ball to arrive and tickles it down to long-leg
Baby boof on strike! on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
lovely late-cut for a four. It was on the off stump line, Cosgrove went back and tapped it ala Lehmaan .
on the middle and leg, turned to the on side
floated up on the middle and leg, coming in , Cosgrove goes back to work it towards midwicket&
slanted across Clarke, who gets his left foot across, covers the stumps, sees there is no inward movement and then, shoulders his arms
again fullish and angled across, Clarke moves forward and across, in the way Ponting does, and lets it go through
whack! it was overpitched slightly, just outside the off stump and Clarke just hit through the line, cleanly, over the mid-off
short and on the middle and leg stump and Clarke executes a lovely short-arm pull, past square-leg.
fullish and outside the off stump, pushed to cover
just short of length, turned around the corner
similar ball, and this time, Cosgrove gets inside the line and works it past square-leg
short and outside the off stump, cut past point
short again but much slower this time, and Cosgrove turns it to midwicket
floated up on the middle stump, driven down the ground the long-on
fullish outside the off stump, driven to mid-off
overpitched on the middle and leg stump, Cosgrove whips it past midwicket
short of length, outside the off stump and Cosgrove looked as he was squared up  but manages to adjust his wrists and taps the ball, down to the third man
a length delivery, on the middle and leg that held its line and Clarke is squared up as he tried to whip it across, gets an leading edge that takes the ball past cover
another length delivery, just on the off stump line, Cosgrove opens the face of the bat, runs it down to point
similar ball and again, Cosgrove runs it down to point.  Very similar to Darren Lehmann.
short and Clarke rocks back and has all the time in the world to dispatch it where he wants. He chose deep midwicket.
tossed up on the middle, turning in slightly, Clarke leans forward, drives it to long-on
fullish on the middle and leg, Cosgrove drives it down to long-on
on the legs, turned around the corner
flatter, quicker and on the leg and middle, turned towards midwicket
on the middle ,fullish, Clarke pushes back, and turns it towards midwicket
right up there, just outside the off stump, Cosgrove attempts to dig it out, doesn't connect well and the ball runs to the off side
short and outside the off stump, enough time in the world to run it down to third man.
short of length, on the middle and leg. Clarke goes back, works his wrists over time, sends the ball into the midwicket gap
in the channel outside the off stump, Clarke leans forward and offers the full face of the bat to it.
on the leg, turning in, Cosgrove goes back and across, tickles it past square-leg
slightly short and quick, Clarke hangs on his back foot and taps the ball to the right of midwicket
floated up, on the legs, Cosgrove turns it around the corner.
tossed up, slower, on the middle stump, driven down the ground
first dot ball of the over. It was on the off stump, on a length but Cosgrove still went back and attempted an late-cut but couldn't beat the short third man
this time he gets the ball to the left of that fielder and they take a single. Five runs, five singles in this over. No risk cricket.
length delivery, angled outside the off stump and Cosgrove hangs on his back foot, opens the face of the bat and runs it down to the third man region
fullish, just outside the off stump and Clarke, as ever, comes forward and offers the full face of the bat in defense

lovely delivery and Clarke is beaten. It was delivered from wide of the crease, landed on a length outside the off stump and didn't shape in as much as Clarke thought it would. Clarke pushed hard at it, searching for the ball and was beaten.
outside the off stump, run down to the third man region

very poor fielding by Bradshaw at mid-off gives free runs to the Australians. It was full and outside the off stump and Cosgrove drove it along the ground but straight to mid-off. should have been stopped but ....     the camera pans to Lara and well ..let me say ...its not an expression that his daughter Sydney would hope to see often.     

Drinks break is on.

lovely late-cut. First ball after the break, was floated just outside the off stump and it turned in slightly, Clarke gave himself room by slightly backing to the leg side and cut it past the wicketkeeper. Clarke is playing a lovely innings here.
full and on the middle and leg, Cosgrove turns it to vacant midwicket spot and they jog through for a quick single
Gayle mis-fields off his own bowling and yields a run. It was driven striaght back to him.
on the leg and middle stump line, attempted to work it through the on side, but doesn't manage to pierce the field.
short of length, on the middle, Clarke gets behind the line and offers the full face of the bat in defence.
way down the leg side and the umpire Asad Rauf has no hesitation in extending his arms
a length delivery, outside the off stump and Clarke hurries onto his front foot and drives it elegantly towards mid-off.
slightly short of length, outside the off stump line, Clarke moves forward, adjusts to the length, opens the face of the blade and runs it down to third man region
wide no 15. Not a proud statistic for the West Indians. way down the leg side.
in the channel outside the offstump, slightly short of length, Cosgrove waits for the ball to arrive, tickles the ball down to third-man
on the hips, short of length, Clarke gets inside the line, flicks it past square-leg

a length-delivery, just on and around the off stump line, Clarke, again comes forward, opens the face of the bat but doesn't find the room to run it down to third-man and has to be contended just pushing it to point
starts off with a overpitched-delivery on the legs, Cosgrove takes his right foot outside the line, and whips it past midwicket
slightly short of length this time and outside the off stump, Cosgrove attempts to cut, but his bottom-hand grip meant he couldn't time it well, ended up running it to point
fuller and on the off stump line, Cosgrove drives it but doesn't quite find his timing and the ball rolls towards mid-off
short and well outside the off stump and Cosgrove reached for it and upper cut it over point. No effort was made to keep it down and the ball runs to cover point fence.
another four, this time a lovely extra cover drive. Hit on-the-up, off his front foot and peirced the field.
pushed towards mid-off and they take a single
a length-delivery on the off stump line, jabbed to point. Clarke wants a single. Cosgrove doesn't.

Got him! a length-delivery, well outside the off stump and Cosgrove tried to hit through the line, on the up but only manages to sting Lara's palms at mid-off. Not a delivery to take a wicket but West Indians won't be complaining. A nice little innings comes to an end.
on the middle and leg, fullish, turned to square-leg
short of length delivery that came in a touch from outside the off stump, Watsone leans forward and pats it back down the track
fuller this time and driven, in the V, to Lara at mid-off
deja-vu. Another wide delivery down the leg side. Wide no 16.
length-delivery that pitched just outside the off stump and headed towards the off, Watson jabs at it and gets an inside edge onto to his pads.
wide outside the off stump but Clarke maybe didn't want to annoy the West Indian fans, reaches out for it and prevents a wide from being called. Hit straight to point

another one outside the off stump, not so wide, swatted past cover and Carlton Baugh, the wicketkeeper, didn't gather the throw from the sweeper cleanly - the ball landed awkwardly in front of him - and an overthrow results.
surprises the batsman with a bouncer. It screamed past the head as Clarke just bends into it and the ball whizzes over his left shoulder
beaten! it was hurled full and just outside the off stump, and it jagged back in off the seam and Watson had a slash at it but ended up driving outside the line
a length-delivery on the middle and off, patted back to the bowler
again punched back down the track
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket.
Its an maiden over. driven down to mid-on.
swing and a miss.  Outside the offstump and Clarke tries to force it away, doesn't connect
on the hips, turned past square-leg and they take a single
on the legs, worked to long-leg
another wide. They must be really rusty!
pushed to the right of mid-on and they jog through for a single
short of length, outside the off stump, Watson attempts to punch it off his back foot but is not able to pierce the ring
fullish and outside the offstump, Watson goes for a drive, finds the cover fielder.
attempted yorker but Clarke takes it on the full, whips it past square-leg, runs hard for two and that's fifty up for Clarke. Its his 18th ODI fifty.
pushed back down the track
another yorker attempted, this one was bang on the target and Clarke manages to dig it out, back to the bowler
short of length, outside the off stump, turned to left of point
Dwayne Smith gets his second wicket.  Landed on a length, and Watson swatted it across the line but straight to the short midwicket fielder.
gets off the mark with a lovely on-drive. It was fullish on the middle and leg, he leant forward, head over the ball and drove it past the midwicket
overpitched on the off stump line, Clarke has a heave, doesn't connect well and it runs down to long-on
fullish ball on off, driven into the covers with a flourish of the bat
slower delivery outside offstump, he lazily late cuts that off the face of the bat and it drops just short of the 'keeper and runs away fine
full on middle and leg, tapped past midwicket and they set off for a sharp single, throw comes in late
full on middle and off, played into the covers
Take that! Smashed through the line, off the meat of the bat, straight back past the bowler and four! That was a cracking shot
fullish and on the stumps, slower ball, worked to the leg side
on the pads and a bit too full, worked through square-leg for a quick couple
just short of a good length, quite full, defended awkwardly to the leg side, quick single pinched
full and dead straight, that's a well bowled yorker, equally well kept out as well
Another one on the up! That is a clean hit. Fullish and outside the off, a full swing of the bat sends the ball back past the bowler and easily beats mid-on
swing and a miss. Normal occurence in the late overs. The hunt for runs is on! Short and wide, Clarke throws his bat at it, doesn't connect though.
swatted away to the off side, doesn't time it well and they hurry through for a single
beaten. full, straight, outside the offstump, Haddin doesn't move his feet, just bends his right knee a bit, tries to cut it, doesn't connect
length-delivery on the stumps, pushed down the ground
whack! slightly short of length, just outside the off stump but Clarke makes room by backing away to the leg side and slashes it over point
fullish on the middle and leg, flicked away to short fine-leg, shy at the non-striker's end, the ball misses the sticks but Clarke had made his ground
on the middle and leg, turned to right of midwicket
full, on the middle stump, driven to left of Taylro at midwicket, who hurls himself and makes a partial stop.
yes sir! the slower ball comes on, just outside the off stump, Clarke is on his front foot, and pats it towards the off side
overpitched, driven down the ground to long-off
fullish, on the middle stump, driven down to long-on
right up there at the blockhole, dug out to cover
fullish, on the off and middle, driven back to the bowler
length-delivery just outside the off stump, Clarke eases forward and whips it, in the air, across the line, past midwicket and they take two
Its all happening! batsman backing to the leg side, the bowler slipping in a slow ball, a jab and the ball is on the pitch and the two batsmen hurry through for a quick single.
turned to right of midwicket
slower ball but landed too short and Haddin pulled it but finds the man at deep midwicket. Just a single.
yorker. right up there. dug out towards cover and just a single results.
another one right up there at the blockhole, dug out again towards midoff
hatrick of yorkers, this one quite didnt land up in the blockhole, Haddin manages to drive it down to long-off
low full-toss this time and Clarke swats it to the deep-midwicket fence.
The leather hunt is on. He walked down the track a bit and heaved it past midwicket fence.
That slower ball does the trick. Released between his thumb and the fore-finger the ball loops in the air and then dips in front of the off stump , beating the slashing blade of Clarke.
Taylor disturbs the furniture. Two wickets in two balls. Haddin attempted to pull a length delivery hurtling towards the off stump, misses and his off stump is pegged back.
Yorker it is. Squeezed out though, down to third man
another yorker attempted but radar is wrong, it ends up outside the off stump and Mitchell Johnson gets his bat down in time and the ball runs past point
right up there at the blockhole, on the middle stump as well. Bracken just about manages to dig it back to the bowler. Very good slog-overs bowling on show here.
got his man this time. Fast, full and straight on the off stump. Bracken goes for a mighty heave, the ball squeezes past the bottom of the flashing blade and crashes into the off stump.
full, fast and straight again but this time Dan Cullen offers the full face of the bat in defense. Taylor gets across to make the stop. No chance of a run.
slow looping slower ball that ends up as a low full-toss as well, swatted to midwicket where Lara dives to his right, makes a half-stop. Not bad for a 37-year old man.

another slower one, this one dipped on the off and middle stump, a ugly hoick across the line was attempted, gets an outside edge and it runs to third man fence. yeah yeah.... its a batsman's game and all that..&
full and outside the off stump, swatted away to long-on
another slower one. lovely bit of deception. It looped and dipped outside the off stump, Cullen adjusts at the last minute, whips it across, over midwicket for a single.
take that! Bravo went round the sticks and sent one full, and Johnson freed his arms, one mighty heave and the ball went in an orbit over long-on.
fullish outside the off stump, driven powerfully to cover
For a change, a bouncer. One for the over. Went over the leg stump.

even before the ball was about to be delivered, Johnson backed away to the leg side, Taylor sent one full and fast, honing in on the off stump. The flashing blade came down in an hurry but the ball evaded it to knock back the off stump.
full and fast again, on the off stump, McGrath makes no initial movement, waits for the ball to arrive and pats it back down the track.
low-full toss results as Taylor goes in for a yorker, McGrath pushes it down the track, towards long-on
another low full-toss, on the off and middle, swatted to the on side
another yorker attempted, Johnson walks forward and across, the ball veers to his foot, he tries to heave it across, doesn't make  contact and they cross over for a run.

inn2.comm: starts off with a jaffa! What a start. Landed on a length, on the seam, around the off stump and moved away and Gayle has a tentative poke at it and is beaten.
drifting down the leg side this time though.
hmm.... another wide, down the leg.
gets his radar right this time. on the off stump line, moving away and Gayle lets it sail harmlessly through to Brad Haddin
on the hips and tucked away behind square-leg

Oh! great ball and what appeared a super 'catch' by Haddin but it had gone of the thigh pad. Good decision by Tony Hill. It landed on the seam, on a length around the middle and off and seamed away. Chanderpaul was squared-up, hang his bat in front of the body, and the cherry moved past it and brushed his thigh pad and went, low, towards first slip and Haddin took off, in the air, with his left glove stretched and came up with the ball.
Another one down the leg. Bit of a mixed over this. A great ball followed up by an wayward delivery
another one and McGrath lets out a yell in frustration
outside the off stump, left alone
fullish, on the leg and middle, hint of swing in, Gayle tries to play a pick-up shot, doesn't connect and it runs off the pads
outside the off stump, full in length, hint of movement away, Chanderpaul keeps his right foot out, covers the stumps and shoulders his arms
finds the edge this time as Chanderpaul pushes at a length-delivery just outside the off stump but the ball drops well short of Ponting at second slipd
the previous one went away, this one came back in sharply. Chanderpaul is surprised by the movement, doubles up and is hit on his thighs.
he takes it away. the seam pointing towards first slip, the ball lands on the seam and curves away, Chanderpaul lets it go through
another outswinger. Chanderpaul covers the stumps, spots the away movement and lets the ball sail into Haddin's gloves.
short of length, around that off stump line, Gayle tries to slash it over point, misses
lands on a length, may be a touch short, around the middle and off, shapes away. Gayle pushes it out towards cover
slightly fuller, outside the off stump and angles away, left alone
another wide. down the leg side. McGrath is seen muttering in anger.
fuller, on the middle, Gayle leans forward, pushes it, past the bowler and to the left of mid-on and they cross over for a single
short of length delivery, on the middle and leg, tucked past square-leg
length-delivery, on the leg and middle, Chanderpaul gets inside the line, tickles it around the corner
fullish, well outside the off stump, Chanderpaul moves towards it, reaches for it as it swings away and is beaten.
full again but this one is close to the off stump, Chanderpaul eases forward, covers the swing and pushes it towards mid-off
starts off outside the off stump and moves further away. left alone.
swing and a miss. another delivery outside the off stump, shaping away and Chanderpaul tries to hit through the line, misses.
a length-delivery around the off stump line, Chanderpaul pushes it out towards point
fullish and this one comes in with the angle but ends up drifting onto the pads. Chanderpaul tries to flick it away, his head falls over a bit and the ball runs off the pads, out to shortish fine-leg
short of length, in the channel around the off stump, steered to backward point
similar delivery, may be bit more bounce, Chanderpaul adjusts his wrists to get on top of it and steers it to point
fuller and on the middle and off, Chanderpaul leans forward, the ball moves away, he adjusts his hands to cover for the movement and taps it to the on side
short of length delivery that landed on the off stump line and shaped back a bit. Chanderpaul tries to force it away, gets cramped and an inside-edge onto his pads results.
for a change, this wide was well outside the off stump
lands on the seam, short of a length, around the middle and it veered back in, doubling up Chanderpaul and rapped him on his thighs.
fullish and outside the off stump and it moves further away. Gayle slashes at it and it goes in the air, out to third man region
whack! short and on the middle, Chanderpaul rocks back to pull it over midwicket.  great shot.
short of length, on the off stump line, pushed towards cover point

almost a caught and bowled. It was full and just outside the off stump, Chanderpaul has a go at it, the bottom-hand takes over, the bat handle rotates in his hands and the ball whizzes past the outstretched left hand of Bracken.
overpitched well outside the off stump, Chanderpaul bends his left knee, reaches out and carves it through the off side ring
similar delivery, maybe not so full and Chanderpaul again tries to thrash it away, but gets an inside edge and the ball runs to the on side
full and on the middle and leg, Gayle hangs back at his crease, whips it across the line, past square-leg
oh ho! Gayle backs away to a length delivery and has a mighty heave, misses. McGrath has a few words to say. I am sure it would have been about how nice a place Malaysia is.

length-delivery on the leg and middle and shaping towards off stump, Chanderpaul is alert though, doesn't try to whip it across the line, waits for the movement, opens the face of the blade and pushes it to the off side
just outside the off stump, McGrath had held the ball across the seam, which meant the ball didn't land on the seam, and it skidded past the tentative poke of Chanderpaul
short of length, punched past cover
Chanderpaul, this time, has one mighty heave. He tried to hit through the line, got under the ball too much and it soared high, landing just short of the boundary ropes near the long-on
Chanderpaul is on a roll here. A fullish delivery, just outside the off stump, he leant forward and just creamed it through the line, between the bowler and the mid-off

almost a catch! It was full again and outside the off stump, Chanders just kept his  right foot out, fetched it from there and swatted it high over midwicket. Johnson chased the cherry and almost got it in the end. The ball landed just in front of his outstretched hands.
Whack! the white ball is flying everywhere. again fetched from outside the off stump, but this time he went for a flat heave over midwicket.
short and outside the off stump, Chanderpaul rocks back and cuts it fiercely, the point fielder makes a half-stop
huh... that one did move. It landed on a length, around the off stump and jagged away off the seam - must have hit a crack- and Chanderpaul's poke was nowhere near the line of the ball.
outside the off stump, left alone this time

ambles in close to the stump, doesn't quite the supporting arm (his right arm) high enough,  and just hurls the cherry. All shoulder. This one kicked up from short of a length and moved away, Chanderpaul adjusted and steered it past point
jaffa! drew Gayle forward and then deserted him. Lovely away movement.
Gayle has had enough poking around. He backs away and swings through the line, but doesn't quite find his timing and the ball drops just short of mid-off
short and rising, on the leg stump line, turned around the corner
slower one. Gayle spots it albeit late in its trajectory, decides against a slog, lets it go through.
a looping slow delivery on the legs, Gayle appeared to have lost sight of it, took his bottom-hand out, swats it away to midwicket
creamed through midwicket. Fullish on the off and middle stump, Chanderpaul leant forward and on-drove it elegantly and powerfully

oh ho! Ala Saeed Anwar! Chanderpaul just walked across his stumps, kept his right foot across, leant forward, got his bat under the ball, a flick of a wrist and the ball soared over long-leg. Great innovation.
Take that! An awesome whack over midwicket. He moves forward, spots the slower one, then leans back a bit and thrashes it over midwicket. The ball flew flat, fast and over the ropes.
Just a dot ball but not without drama. Chanderpaul walks down a bit and tries a mighty heave-ho. misses and Haddin gathers it
Gayle gets Chanderpaul back on strike. What will happen now?
short of length, on the middle and off stump line, pushed to midwicket
89.0 mph delivery, honing in on the legs, Chanderpaul tries to flick, misses and a loud shout for lbw goes up but it was going down the leg
Chanderpaul rocks on. Fifty up. Short and on the middle and leg, Chanderpaul leans back and short-arm pulls it to the long-leg fence
length-delivery outside the off stump, Chanderpaul tries to thrash it through the ring, doesn't time it well and the ball runs to the off side.

better delivery. It kicked up from a length, around the off stump line, Chanderpaul hurries back, has a jab at it, gets an inside-edge which takes the ball rolling past the stumps, towards the keeper.
slanted across Gayle, well outside the off stump and Gayle has a slash, but doesn't connect.
again a clear effort to slant it across, outside the off stump. Gayle watches it sail into the gloves of Haddin.
cracking cut! Again angled across, Gayle keeps his back foot across and forces it past point.

almost a catch! would have been a great one if Clarke had held on. Gayle had slashed at a slightly wide and full delivery outside the off stump and it went off the outside edge, over point and Clarke, running backwards, threw himself at the cherry but only to grasp thin air.
sailing past the off stump, to the wicketkeeper
another one outside the off stump, Gayle lets it go through to Haddin
banged in short and on the off and middle stump line, Gayle pulls it down onto the ground, and into the midwicket gap and they run two.
another one flies over midwicket. A length delivery on the middle stump line, Chanderpaul just clears his front foot from the line of the ball and heaves it over midwicket
short of length, just outside the off stump, Chanderpaul cuts it powerfully to point
banged in short, outside the off stump and Chanderpaul goes back, and swats it - a tennis shot- back down the track, between the bowler and mid-on.

Its just not slogging. a touch of artistry here. It was fullish, on the off stump line, no room for cut. Chanderpaul leans back, and with soft hands , lets the ball come onto him and taps it gently down to the third man region
Gayle decides to join in the fun. Creames a fullish delivery on the off stump, over mid-on!
Whack every ball contest continues! Full and outside the off stump and what does Gayle do, he just thrashes it flat and fast over the cover for a six!
ooh almost caught by Ponting at cover. Chanderpaul tried to force a short of length delivery off his back foot, doesn't quite time it well and it pops up but lands just in front of Ponting.
clever change of pace. full and outside the off stump, Chanderpaul tries to reach it to glide it through to third man, misses.
length-delivery on the off stump line, in fact just outside and moving further away, Chanderpaul moves towards it, opens the face of the bat and steerts it to point
short and rising chest high. around the off stump. Chanderpaul is a bit surprised, adjusts at the last minute, works his wrists overtime to get on top of the ball to keep it down.
fullish, outside the off stump, Chanderpaul tries to steer it past slips, doesn't connect. Its a no-ball.
full and wide of the offstump, Chanderpaul chases it but makes no contact
good length on middle and off, played to midwicket, doesnt chance the fielder's arm
Shot! Full on offstump, Gayle steps away and carves that over point for four, a real sliced sqaure cut, Johnson not happy
Thwack! Incredible shot! Gayle backs away again, exposing all his stumps, and thumps that off the back foot straight over the bowler for four
Short of a length on off, Gayle stands tall and runs that down to third man
good ball on and around off, not too full and he punches that into the covers off the back foot, a dot ball, ho ho ho...
Maximum! No matter where they bowl it, runs are flowing! This one is banged in short, Chanderpaul goes for some sort of ungainly hook and gets a top edge that flies over third man for six, hoo hah!
bouncer! took off from the middle of the track, flew over the middle stump, Gayle attempts a weak hook shot, doesn't connect.
Classic Gayle shot! Backing away to the leg side, exposing the stump and a fierce thump off the back-foot and the ball screams past a diving mid-off fielder
slower one, on the middle and off, Gayle waits for the ball, drives it along the ground to long-on. (Ponting had pushed the man back after the earlier four)
short and rising, on the leg and middle, Chanderpaul walks across, takes the bottom-hand out of the handle, swats it away to shortish-fine-leg.
floated on the off stump line, patted gently back down the track
on the off and middle, Chanderpaul drives it inside-out, to deep cover
tossed up on the leg and middle, Gayle takes his front foot outside the line and thumped it between the bowler and the long-on (who is wide) and another four!
comes down the track and hits it straight back to the bowler.
Reverse sweep is out as well! outside the off stump and he slaps it past the short third-man.. cosgrove makes a valiant chase and hurls himself near the ropes but can't prevent the boundary.
on the leg and middle, Gayle tries to whip it across the line, gets an leading edge, and out towards long-on
short of length, on the off stump line, Chanderpaul pats it gently to the left of point and they hurry through for a single.
Incredible shot! Short delivery, chest high on the off stump line, Gayle rocks back to pull it flat and the ball screams over midwicket.
fuller and outside the off stump, Gayle reaches out, plays it past cover
fullish on the legs, worked past square-leg
swing and a miss. Angled across Gayle, full in length, Gayle goes for a slash, doesn't connect.
gone! Australians get rid of Gayle. It was a fullish delivery, pitched outside the off stump and slanting away, Gayle bends down, and tries to chop it past point, instead steers it straight to point.
tossed up on the middle and off stump line, Chanderpaul comes down the track to drive it to long-on
on the middle and leg stump line, Sarwan keeps his left foot across, outside the line, turns it around the corner
outside the off stump, driven down to the sweeper cover
tossed up outside the leg stump, turning in slightly, Chanderpaul takes his right foot outside the line, whips it to deep midwicket. Lovely skilful shot.
outside the leg stump, whipped to deep midwicket again.
fullish on the middle and off stump line, backed towards the leg side and forced away to mid-off

what drama here! A great shot, almost caught at the ropes, was it a six or a four or just what they ran?   Its a six! Chanderpaul just whipped a fullish delivery, on the stumps, high and over deep mid-wicket and it dropped down near the ropes. McGrath was there and caught the ball as he back-pedalled a bit but in the process went over the rope and he threw the ball back inside the arena. But by then he had stepped on the ropes
a length delivery that jagged back in from the off stump, cramping Sarwan. But Sarwan manages to jab it down, to the off side.
streaky four! Full and outside the off stump and Sarwan throws his bat at it, gets an outside-edge and it flies past the slips and crashes into the third-man fence
beaten. Full and outside the off stump and again Sarwan ends up driving inside the line but doesn't get a touch.
A length-delivery that landed just outside the off stump and stayed out. Chanderpaul has heave across the line, misses.
Runs continue to come! Four overthrows! tapped close to the of side and they ran through, Ponting swoops in from cover and has a shy at the sticks, and it rebounds off it, to the fine-leg fence.
oh ho! Sarwan lets a ball go through and that one jagged back in and ended up bouncing over the middle stump. Both the bowler and the batsman have a chuckle over it.
just outside the off stump and this time it stays out, Sarwan shoulders his arms
beaten outside the off stump, Similar ball and this time, Sarwan tries to cut it, too close for that.
length delivery on the off stump, swatted to mid-on
short and rising, flies over the right shoulder of Chanderpaul who goes for a hook, misses.
fullish, on the off stump line, Chanderpaul attempts to drive it , doesnt time it well and the ball rolls towards mid-off
beaten. a lovely delivery. landed on a length, just on the off stump line and shaped away to beat a tentative poke.
another one flies past the outside edge. Full and angling across, Chanderpaul keeps his right foot out, and has a slash, doesn't connect.
right up there at the blockhole, just outside the off stump, steered away to the third-man region
on the off and middle ,full in length, pushed towards cover
slower ball, on the blockhole, around the off and middle, pushed out to mid-off
Chanderpaul charges down the track, has a mighty go at a length delivery just outside the off stump, misses.
walks across the stumps to a short of length delivery and whips it to long-leg. Chanderpaul continues to innovate and express himself.
back of a length delivery, just outside the off stump and Sarwan tries to steer it to third man and is beaten.
cracker of a delivery. fullish, on a length outside the off stump and it kicked up a bit. Sarwan pushes at it, ends up playing inside the line
slightly slower delivery, outside the off stump but short in length. Sarwan cuts it but cuts straight to point
Sarwan breaks free. Another short delivery, just outside the off stump and this time Sarwan makes sure he beats the point fielder.
and he's welcomed back with a thumping pull over midwicket for four, thanks very much says Chanderpaul
and again, this time he opts for a rank half-volley outside off and Chanderpaul pummels that on the up between cover and mid-off, tremendous shot, this is murder!

and it works! Bangs this one in short of a length on off, Chanderpaul looks to run that fine but the bounce surprises him and all he can do is feather a thin edge through to Haddin and Johnson gets the man who has creamed fours to all parts of the park on this awesome evening, what an innings he played when sent up the order to open
ooooh, close! Overpitched outside the off stump and he flays at this one first-up, zero footwork and he almost drags it on, edges past the stumps to fine leg
full on middle and leg, flicked very fine for a single
good length on off, Lara shuffles and tries to defend on the hop, ends up turning it fine and they try and sneak through for a quick single as square leg swoops in, decided against it
good length on off, leaden-footed chop into the covers
similar ball and again he just stands there and drives into the ground on the offside
beauty that lands on off and cuts him in half, went through everything and hit nothing, well mixed up on the pace there is the wily McGrath
fuller outside off and Sarwan shoulders arms
slight width offered, he goes for a cut and chops that past point for a brace

the big man goes, oh ho! Goes back to a full, swinging delivery on off that cuts in and Lara is caught hopping right on the stumps, umpire says yep, thats out and West Indies have lost two big wickets in no time, Johnson strikes again, can he pull things around for Australia?
good length on middle and off, defends off the backfoot with a full face of the bat
this one is wider of off and swinging away, he leaves it with a stride forward
similar ball, slightly shorter, again he gets right behind the line and defends, good ball
another similar ball on the stumps, some bounce, he negotiates it well and turns that to the onside
another tidy ball outside the stumps and its left alone
short of length, on the off, punched to cover
length delivery, outside the off stump, Sarwan doesn't move towards the ball, stands there and tries to square-drive, misses.
fullish delivery, just outside the off stump and Sarwan ends up searching for it. A nervous poke results and he is beaten.
beaten again! full and just outside the off stump drawing Sarwan forward and straightens after pitching. Sarwan is beaten as he pushes inside the line.
overpitched on the middle and leg, Bravo leans forward and on-drives it straight to mid-on
almost caught behind, down the leg side. It was flicked away, very fine and Hadding flung himself to his left but doesn't get a touch.
on the leg and middle again, turned past midwicket
short of length, just outside the off stump, Sarwan goes back and punches it to point
banged in short, on the off stump line, Sarwan rocks back, pulls it , straight into the ground, out to long-leg
lovely looking cover drive. right up there for the shot and Bravo leans into it, left elbow high and punch-drives it to left of cover but a good tumbling stop there denies him a certain four.
Poor shot sends Bravo packing! It was short of length, outside the off stump and Bravo tries to fetch it from there - a attempted pull shot- and it pops up, off the leading edge, to cover.
fullish, outside the off stump, Hinds leans forward to steer it to the third-man region
short of length delivery, outside the off stump, Sarwan hops back and punches it out to cover.
on the hips, worked to square-leg.
In the channel outside the off stump, short of length, left alone
fuller this time, outside the off, gives room for Sarwan to drive square, past the diving Clarke at point
thrashed through the cover! A length delivery, slanted across, Sarwan goes back and across and punches it, in the air, past cover.
fullish on the middle stump, Sarwan looked unsure whether to go back or forward, stayed where he was and pushed it weakly back to the bowler.
short and wide, creamed over cover point, out to the sweeper cover.
fullish, on the middle, Hinds is caught at the crease, manages to push it towards square-leg and they rush through for a single.
bouncer that caught Sarwan by surprise. He attempted to pull, but pulled out of the shot in the end as the ball climbed on him rather quickly.
short of length delivery, on the off stump line, Sarwan hops back, has a jab at it, gets an inside edge and the ball rolls near his feet.
fullish, bit of scrambled seam which took the pace off the ball, Sarwan drove it straight and by the time the mid-off came across to make the stop, the batsmen had crossed over.
on the middle and leg, turned around the corner.

Cosgrove gets a wicket! Gentle seam-up stuff, landed on a length, around the off stump and shaped away a bit, Hinds pushed at it with an open-face of the bat and ends up gliding it straight into the gloves of Haddin.
another length delivery, on the middle stump, Smith pushes it towards midwicket, both batsmen initially want a run, both, then, decide against it and they retreat back into their positions in time.
slightly short of length, on the off stump line, punched to cover
short of length, outside the off stump and Dwayne Smith tries to force it off his back foot, hits it straight to short cover
just outside the off stump, steered to the third-man region
beaten outside the off stump. A straight ball actually, did nothing spectacular but Sarwan tried to poke at it in an effort to run it down to thrid man.
drifting onto the pads, tries to tickle it away, doesn't connect and the ball runs off the pads to Haddin. Sarwan wants a run, Smith doesn't and sends the striker back into his crease.
this one kept low. Sarwan brings his bat down in time to keep it away.
short of length, on the off and middle, Sarwan stays beside the line, and taps it out towards cover
banged in short and on the leg stump line, Sarwan tries to pull but gloves it and the ball pops over the stumps and rolls to the wicketkeeper.

The pull shot leads to his demise again. Sarwan pulls a shortish ball, fetching it from outside the offstump, doesn't get much meat behind it and it goes to right of Ponting at short midwicket who takes a couple of steps and then dives to take a good smart catch. Advantage Australia.
angled across the off stump, left alone.
short of length, on the middle and off, Baugh hops back and taps it to the on side.
fullish and outside the off stump, Baugh goes back and across, covers his stumps and shoulders arms
lands on a length, around the off stump and goes with the angle, Baugh pushes at it but stays inside the line of the ball.

Another one goes..... Wicket no 7 falls. Wide outside the off stump and Baugh gets a brain-explosion: throws his bat at it, only to get a faint nick behind and huge smiles erupt in the Australian faces as Haddin gloves it comfortably.
fullish on the leg and middle, beats an attempted flick shot and thuds into the pads.
short of length delivery, outside the off stump, Smith pushes at it, gets an thick outside edge and McGrath, at third-man, moves smartly to his left to make the stop.
Australia are all over the West Indians. Full, fast, and straightens after pitching on the middle stump. Bradshaw is caught plumb in front as he tries to whip it across the line.

And then they were one. Yorker, right on the middle stump line, disturbs the furniture as Taylor goes for a cover drive, the bat slicing through thin air as the cherry evades it to crash into the middle.
overpitched on the off and middle stump line, driven to cover

lovely slower ball to finish the over. It looped up on the off stump line and then dipped rapidly, catching Edwards by surprise. He hangs his bat out, and luckily, for him the ball pops over the short cover fielder.
fullish on the leg stump line, worked to right of mid-on
Smith fishes at one outside the off stump and is beaten.

That's it, its all over. Australia have won. Fullish delivery in the channel outside the offstump, angling away and Smith, the last hope for West Indies, pushed at it, got an edge and Hadding pouched it with glee. Bracken turns to appeal, gets the nod he was looking for, turns, and runs over to his teammates to join in the celebratory huddle.
